
msgid "Configuring clusters"
msgstr ""

msgid "Enterprise Edition"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|tcm_full_name| is a part of the `Enterprise Edition "
"<https://www.tarantool.io/compare/>`_."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|tcm_full_name| features a built-in text editor for Tarantool EE cluster "
"configurations."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"When you :ref:`connect a cluster <tcm_connect_cluster>` to |tcm|, it gains "
"access to the cluster's centralized configuration storage: an etcd or a "
"Tarantool cluster. |tcm| has both read and write access to the cluster "
"configuration. This enables the configuration editor to work in two ways:"
msgstr ""

msgid "If a configuration already exists, the editor shows its current state."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"When you change the configuration in the editor and apply changes, they are "
"sent to the configuration storage."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To learn how to write Tarantool cluster configurations, see "
":ref:`configuration`."
msgstr ""

msgid "Managing a cluster's configuration"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The configuration editor is available on the **Cluster** > **Configuration**"
" page."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To start managing a cluster's configuration, select this cluster in the "
"**Cluster** drop-down and go to the **Configuration** page."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"A cluster configuration in |tcm| can consist of one or multiple YAML files. "
"When there are multiple files, they are all considered parts of a single "
"cluster configuration. You can use this for structuring big cluster "
"configurations. All files that form the configuration of a cluster are "
"listed on the left side of the **Cluster configuration** page."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To add a cluster configuration file, click the plus icon (**+**) below the "
"page title."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To open a configuration file in the editor, click its name in the file list."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To delete a cluster configuration file, click the **Delete** button beside "
"the filename."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To download a cluster configuration file, click the **Download** button "
"beside the filename."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"All configuration changes are discarded when you leave the **Cluster "
"configuration** page. :ref:`Save <tcm_configuring_clusters_save>` the "
"configuration if you want to continue editing it later or :ref:`apply "
"<tcm_configuring_clusters_apply>` it to start using it on the cluster."
msgstr ""

msgid "Saving a configuration draft"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"|tcm| can store configurations drafts. If you want to leave an unfinished "
"configuration and return to it later, save it in |tcm|. Saving applies to "
"whole cluster configurations: it records the edits of all files, file "
"additions, and file deletions."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To save a cluster configuration draft after editing, click **Save** in the "
"**Cluster configuration** page."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"All unsaved changes are discarded when you leave the **Cluster "
"configuration** page."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"If you have a saved configuration draft, you can reset the changes for each "
"of its files individually. A reset returns the file into the state that is "
"currently used by a cluster (that is, saved in the configuration storage). "
"If you reset a newly added file, it is deleted."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To reset a saved configuration file, click the **Reset** button beside the "
"filename."
msgstr ""

msgid "Applying a configuration"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"When you finish editing a configuration and it's ready to use, apply the "
"updated configuration to the cluster. To apply a cluster configuration, "
"click **Apply** on the **Cluster configuration** page. This sends the new "
"configuration to the cluster configuration storage, and it comes into effect"
" upon the cluster configuration reload."
msgstr ""
